Does My Business Need Workplace Compliance and HR Consulting Services?

Even though you won’t have the HR worries of a large business with one hundred employees, you still need to have appropriate HR and safety procedures in place. Because if something does go wrong, you need to have these procedures to fall back on.

A lack of policies and procedures can open your business up to untold instability and can significantly increase the risk of business failure. Something small can have a huge impact on the solidity and security of your team and with every team member in a small business filling a vital role, it is vital that you have the procedures in place to protect them and your business.

Many of our clients come to us for help with some of the issues below and stay because of the stability and support that having a dedicated HR consultant by your side can provide. The peace of mind you get knowing that your business is protected and supported by procedures is not to be underestimated.

How Our Human Resource Consulting Works

These steps are a broad overview of how our human resource consulting services work. If you would like to know more about any of these stages or to find out more about how you can start with us, then please call us to discuss your business needs.

Step 1

When you partner with our HR consulting Brisbane team, the first step we take is to meet with you and go through your business structure. Our workplace compliance professionals can identify your opportunities for improvement and discuss particular services you would like to implement.

Step 2

A dedicated HR consultant will then complete a gap analysis where we focus on what you currently have in place, where you would like to be, and how we can fill in this space with procedures and processes tailored to your business.

Step 3

We’ll create a proposal which outlines everything we have discussed and deliver a scope of work for your approval.

Step 4

After you have signed off on the outlined processes and proposed work, we will discuss pricing and prepare to start work.

Step 5

Final confirmation, you’re on board as a client, and we can begin work!

— Bramwell Partners
